<div id="header-info" class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-lg-6">
      <p>The “Dakota Access” Pipeline (DAPL) is a $3.8B, fracked-oil pipeline currently under construction in North Dakota (USA), crossing the lands of the Standing Rock Sioux Nation. This construction is threatening the water of 18 million people living downstream and is violating the sovereignty of the First Peoples.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-lg-6">
      <p>
        You are in Berlin and want to stand in solidarity with Standing Rock against the Dakota Access Pipeline? <!-- a bit bigger, to call the attention -->
        This page is offering you a way to take direct-action and be part of the movement, uplifting <b>indigenous sovereignty</b> and <b>climate justice</b>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>


<div id="content" class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-lg-6">
      <h1>What we do</h1>
      <p>The <a href="http://www.defunddapl.org/">#deFundDAPL global campaign</a> was initiated by the water protectors at Standing Rock and is taking place throughout the month of December. The goal is to pressure the banks funding the pipeline to terminate their investments and use the allmighty power of money against the system.
        There are <a href="http://www.foodandwaterwatch.org/news/who's-banking-dakota-access-pipeline" target="_blank">two german financial institutions</a> banking the pipeline: Deutsche Bank and Bayern LB (DKB being the 100% subsidiary company of the Bayern LB).
        <!-- We decided to focus on <b>Deutsche Bank</b> as they have a lot of branches in Berlin and are the biggest investor with <b>275$ million</b>.</p> -->
      <p>Hence, we are calling for a collective direct-action: <b>DeFundDAPL takes over X-mas markets!</b>
        The idea is to empower little groups to take direct action, simultaneously over the course of next week at different Christmas markets listed below.
        The main purpose of the action is:
        <ul>
          <li>to raise awareness about what's happening in Standing Rock and the DeFund DAPL campaign</li> </ul>

        You can also...
        <ul>
          <li>Invite people to contact their banks through phone or email <i>more details on the flyer</i></li>
            <li>Bake delicious cookies and <!-- link-->raise donations for the water protectors</li>
          </ul>

        <!--at different branches of the Deutsche Bank. With this action, the groups will distribute flyers with the 2 goals in mind:
        <ol>
          <li>Inform people about the situation in Standing Rock and convince them that they can do something about it now!</li>
          <li>After talking to the people, ask them to go talk to the bank staff and eventually close their bank accounts, following the guidelines.</li>
        </ol>
-->
      </p>
    </div>
